Season 1 in the books! Here’s the cast and crew of Fantasy Football Pregame with Matthew Berry …. When I came to @nbcsports it was in early August. The idea of launching one brand new show, let alone two (our daily show as well) was daunting to say the least. We would be on the air in less than a month. I had no idea if we could even pull off a live, two hour show every single Sunday and then if we did… would anyone watch it?

We did… and then some. People watched on @peacocktv and it did so well we got picked up by @cnbc as well. So incredibly grateful for the entire cast & crew especially my co-hosts @themichaelsmith & @croucherjd. Appreciate @profootballtalk joining us every week to drop knowledge. Special shout-out to our producers @augiedogie @d_bro1389 & @damilatis and crack researcher @blakefriedman23. 

A very special thank you to our sponsors @applebees & @betmgm for their tremendous support throughout the year as well. They’ve been great partners. 

And of course, shout-out to our friends at @nflpa for all the set decorations. 

But most importantly everyone that watched, tweeted, engaged with or even just spent a few seconds on a video we posted to a social channel before scrolling past. I appreciate and love you all. 

We will see you next year!
Via the #FFHappyHour podcast @peacocktv @croucherjd @lorddontlose @cdcarter13

Broadcast my very first show from the Super Bowl today. Legit. I’ve been to many Super Bowls and done time on radio row being interviewed but my former place never had me broadcasting from SB. Not on my show or any of the other NFL shows. But then today I walk up and there’s a set and a sigh with my name on it. And a list of big name guests that are coming on all week. So another milestone for me today. We talked some news and free agency and Super Bowl props and made a bunch of jokes and it was great. We will be broadcasting @peacock live all week and it’ll be on demand on the NFL on NBC YouTube channel and whereever you get your podcasts. But I don’t know man. It was just cool. Having so much fun.

So a number of years ago the Fantasy Sports & Gaming Association named an award after me. The Matthew Berry Game Changer award given yearly to those, who, well, changed the game. Who advanced fantasy sports and/or sports betting industry in a brand new and meaningful way. I’m humbled by the honor but it’s also gives me the thrill of getting to give it out every year. Not sure there’s a more deserving winner than @nigeleccles who co-founded FanDuel, redefined what it means to play fantasy sports, created a whole new category of gaming in DFS and based on the success of FanDuel, was a catalyst in PASPA being overturned and sports betting becoming legal in this country.

*ROUND OF APPLAUSE* 👏

First of many awards for #FFHappyHour!

#fantasyfootball #nfl #sportsbetting #sports #awards

Story time: So because of a previously scheduled family vacation, I had to leave the Fantasy Sports & Gaming Association conference early. Which means I missed Fantasy Football Happy Hour winning the award for Best Audio Content - Enterprise division (ie from a big company). Just incredible. Sappy note time. But I am just so blown away by this. 

You guys have no idea how nervous I was when I left ESPN. Would people find me? I had spent 15 years building something at ESPN. At a time when there was a lot less competition. Could I do it again? Could I find like minded people to help me build it? Could I develop chemistry with new co-hosts? 

To @nbcsports credit they said to me repeatedly “We are in this with you for the long haul. We know this will take time.” I never felt pressure. Just love and support. @pbevacqua @samflood2222 @rick_cordella @mmehta6 

Well. 

Everything this year was better than expected but I still could never have imagined this. Winning this award over some really great podcasts that have been around much longer? In our first year? As voted on by all of our peers & colleagues in the fantasy sports and sports betting community? (The people who really know)?

Incredible. Unreal. Thank you @croucherjd @connorjamesrogers @lorddontlose for being awesome on air all year. 

Thank you to the entire @nbcsportsedge family for their production, support and promotion. I’m sure I’ll forget someone but @d_bro1389 @augiedogie @damilatis @ryanburke88 @blakefriedman23 @alexafiesta @mattcasey9  @adambwise @dcranin @jskarp and his social team and our long lost NHL brother @brubin91 

Thanks to our great partners @applebees & @betmgm for amazing support and encouragement all year long. 

Thank you to all the guests this year - from NFL superstars, celebrities and our other NBC colleagues like @simmsunbuttoned @profootballtalk Jason Garrett @themichaelsmith Denny Carter and Pat Kerrane 

And thanks, MOST OF ALL to everyone who came & found us. You mean more to me than you will ever know. And true best part is… if you loved this year, wait till next season when we actually have more than two weeks to plan. Love you all. 🙏❤️

Ok personal story time that I should’ve done like two weeks ago but took a while to get all the photos. Anyways, read this before scrolling. I promise it’s worth it. 

As long time readers might be aware, my 18 year old @cmoran.24 is the starting D-Mid for Cheshire High School here in CT. That’s him - #24. 

And recently, Cheshire was in the finals of the SCC Tournament. The SCC is the Southern Connecticut Conference & it’s made up of schools of different sizes and classifications. 

Facing Cheshire in the finals was Fairfield Prep. And Prep is, well, a super power. It’s a private school that is very well funded, sits on a 200 acre campus and heavily recruits athletes throughout the country. They have won the SCC title each of the past six seasons. They are a “Class L” school (meaning Large) & the last time Cheshire beat them was 2010. 

Before the game I met a father from Fairfield Prep. He recognized me. Nice guy, he ran a private equity hedge fund, he told me. And mentioned how well they recruit. 

Meanwhile, Cheshire, well, Cheshire is a typical small CT city. Cheshire High is a public “Class M” school (Medium) & all the kids who play for Cheshire are town kids. They grew up here. I’ve seen these same kids play together since they were in 2nd and 3rd grade. I know the kids, I’m friends with the parents, I’ve watched them all grow up into great lacrosse players and better people. 

But again. It’s just the kids we have in our town. We can’t go grab a defenseman from Rhode Island because we need one and give them room and board and a scholarship and who knows what else. 

It is against this backdrop my kid and his friends, many of them juniors and seniors he’s grown up with, faced off against #1 seed Fairfield Prep in the SCC Finals, trying to beat them for the 1st time in 13 years. 

The game was very chippy & tight all night, the two teams trading goals back and forth. And at the end of regulation…. It was tied. 7-7. 

So now it’s sudden death overtime. Next goal wins. And in OT…Cheshire wins the face-off. And after a tough clear, Cheshire calls time-out. Out of the time-out, Cheshire takes the ball (they’re in black) & then…this happens.
